To create an array in Java with 3 elements and fill it with the numbers 3, 4, and 7, you can use the following code:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Declare and initialize the array with 3 elements
        int[] numbers = {3, 4, 7};

        // Output the array elements
        for (int number : numbers) {
            System.out.println(number);
        }
    }
}
```

In this code, we declare an integer array named `numbers` and initialize it with the values 3, 4, and 7. The `for-each` loop is then used to print each element of the array.
